<subSubSection id="B4F06548B118A138EBFDFE0BE365FCB2" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC5536C3B118A138EBFDFE0BE365FCB2" blockId="20.[151,1436,402,823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138EBFDFE0BE151FE76" bold="true" box="[199,315,474,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B118A138E88AFE0AE444FE76" box="[944,1070,474,499]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="karroica">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138E88AFE0AE444FE76" box="[944,1070,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. karroica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EF4EFE0BE540FE76" author="Loveridge" box="[1140,1322,474,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Loveridge, A. (1947) Revision of the African lizards of the Family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 98, 1 - 469, pls. 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1947">
Loveridge 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EFD4FE0AE540FE76" box="[1262,1322,475,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EE0FFE0BE0B8FD92" author="Wermuth" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Wermuth, H. (1965) Liste der rezenten Amphibien und Reptilien, Gekkonidae, Pygopodidae, Xantusiidae. Das Tierreich, 80, xxii + 246 pp." type="book" year="1965">
Wermuth 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EBADFE2FE0B8FD92" box="[151,210,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Branch 
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138EA0CFE2EE10DFD92" box="[310,359,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EA4FFE2EE1DAFD92" box="[373,432,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1988.0">1988</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EA86FE2FE228FD92" author="Kluge" box="[444,578,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (1991) Checklist of Gekkonid lizards. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 85, 1 - 35. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 23317515.85.1" type="journal article" year="1991">Kluge 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138E974FE2EE2EDFD92" author="Kluge" box="[590,647,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (1993) Checklist of Gekkonid Lizards. International Gecko Society, San Diego, 245 pp." type="book" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
) but was elevated to specific status by 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EF05FE2EE4BBFD92" author="Bates" box="[1087,1233,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Bates, M. F. (1996) In search of the elusive flat geckos of the eastern Free State. Culna 51, 13 - 15." type="journal article" year="1996">
Bates (
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EFB7FE2FE4A3FD92" box="[1165,1225,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, although without substantial discussion, and some later authors, especially outside of 
<collectingCountry id="84FD7653B118A138E88BFDF3E42DFDBE" box="[945,1095,546,571]" name="South Africa" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, have continued to include it within 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B118A138EBD0FD96E104FDDA" box="[234,366,582,607]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="karroica">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138EBD0FD96E104FDDA" box="[234,366,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. karroica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EA85FD97E221FDDA" author="Kluge" box="[447,587,582,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (2001) Gekkotan lizard taxonomy. Hamadryad, 26, 1 - 209." type="journal article" year="2001">
Kluge 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138E935FD96E221FDDA" box="[527,587,583,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). One subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B118A138E813FD96E3AAFDDA" box="[809,960,582,607]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="karroica" subSpecies="wilmoti">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138E813FD96E3AAFDDA" box="[809,960,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. k. wilmoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has been variously recognized as valid (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EBA4FDBBE10BFD06" author="FitzSimons" box="[158,353,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="FitzSimons, V. F. (1943) The lizards of South Africa. Memoirs of the Transvaal Museum, 1, i - xv + 1 - 528, + 24 pls + map." type="journal article" year="1943">
FitzSimons 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EA12FDBAE10BFD06" box="[296,353,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or not (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EAFFFDBBE217FD06" author="Loveridge" box="[453,637,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Loveridge, A. (1947) Revision of the African lizards of the Family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 98, 1 - 469, pls. 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1947">
Loveridge 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138E978FDBAE217FD06" box="[578,637,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138E9B1FDBBE34AFD06" author="Branch" box="[651,800,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Branch, W. R. (1981) An annotated checklist of the lizards of the Cape Province, South Africa. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums (Natural History), 13, 141 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">
Branch 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138E9DEFDBAE34AFD06" box="[740,800,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Its status is under review (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EF5AFDBAE536FD06" author="Bates" box="[1120,1372,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Branch, W. R. (1998) Taxonomy and distribution of the Afroedura nivaria and A. karroica complexes (Sauria: Gekkonidae). Herpetological Association of Africa, Fifth Symposium, University of Stellenbosch, 14 - 16 September 1998, Programme and Abstracts. [2 unnumbered pages]" type="book chapter" year="1998">
Bates &amp; Branch 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EE1AFDBAE536FD06" box="[1312,1372,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Our sampling included a single specimen resembling 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B118A138E984FD5EE37AFD22" box="[702,784,654,679]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="halli">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138E984FD5EE37AFD22" box="[702,784,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. halli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was deeply divergent from all other samples (
<figureCitation id="64D12A46B118A138EE73FD5FE5E0FD22" box="[1353,1418,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,490,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[147,1432,481,1677]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood phylogram of Afroedura relationships derived from two genes (ND 2, RAG 1). Support values are presented as maximum likelihood bootstraps (MLBS) / Bayesian posterior probabilities (BPP) / parsimony bootstraps (PBS). Only most closely related outgroup taxa are shown. Images (top to bottom) of representative Afroedura species groups: A. hawequensis, A. pondolia, A. karroica, A. loveridgei, A. haackei, A. marleyi, A. granitica sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250496/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EE47FD5EE5E0FD22" box="[1405,1418,655,679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), supporting the findings of 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B118A138EAF8FD63E2EBFD4E" author="Makhubo" box="[450,641,690,715]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Makhubo, B. G. (2013) Phylogenetic and Morphological Analysis of the Afroedura nivaria (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) Species Complex in South Africa. Unpublished M. Sc. Thesis, University of Stellenbosch, xiii + 106 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Makhubo (
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138E906FD62E213FD4E" box="[572,633,691,715]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who found multiple divergent clades within the species. Although the distinctiveness of this specimen in our two-gene analysis may be artificially high due to the absence of RAG 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EEA9FD06E5F6FD6A" box="[1427,1436,727,751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.0">1</number>
sequence (Table 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EA6BFD2AE10BFC96" box="[337,353,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2.0">2</number>
), the&gt; 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EA94FD2AE1A1FC96" box="[430,459,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="20.0">20</number>
% ND 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138E92BFD2AE274FC96" box="[529,542,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2.0">2</number>
divergence from typical 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B118A138E80EFD2AE3ECFC96" box="[820,902,762,787]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="halli">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B118A138E80EFD2AE3ECFC96" box="[820,902,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. halli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which vary among themselves by 
<number id="4A2224E4B118A138EE34FD2AE5E9FC96" box="[1294,1411,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.61" valueMax="3.02" valueMin="0.2">0.20â€“3.02</number>
%, supports the view that this represents a different species.
</paragraph>
